# Tenant identifier denylist

The strings below are banned anywhere in this repository (source, tests,
fixtures, comments, CHANGELOG, release notes, commit messages). The
`Tenant-name denylist` CI job greps the working tree on every push / PR
and fails the build if any match is found.

If you need a placeholder for documentation or fixtures, use one of:

- `ACME` (default contract-number prefix)
- `Acme Procurement Co.` / `AcmeProcure` (default company name / short name)
- `示例公司` (Chinese placeholder)
- `TENANT-...` (when illustrating that tenants supply their own value)

## Banned literals

- Acme
- ACME
- acme
- jqdomain

Any production-tenant-specific identifier that lands in code MUST be
configurable via `system_parameters` (see `contract.number_prefix` for
the canonical pattern), never hard-coded.
